{"lemma":"عَتْمَةٌ","slug":"عَتْمَةٌ","root":"ع.ت.م","root_slug":"ع-ت-م","root_link":"/words/roots/ع-ت-م","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":1},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n27991"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B9%D9%8E%D8%AA%D9%92%D9%85%D9%8E%D8%A9%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"darkness"}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/ʕa.ta.ma/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n27991","headword_ar":"عَتَمَةٌ","root":"Etm","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Slowness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tardiness:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IB, TA:) hence the saying of a rájiz,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"bi*iY salamo \n                      \n                     \n                        TayofN A^alamo\n                      \n                     \n                        bayona Alxayamo \n                      \n                      ↓ \n      yasoriY Eatamo"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yasoriY baTiyoy^FA","text_ar":"يَسْرِى بَطِيْيًا"},{"kind":"text","text":", [i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A phantom visited"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^alamo","text_ar":"اَلَمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"being for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^alam~a","text_ar":"اَلَمَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in Dhoo-Selem, journeying by night slowly amid the tents,"},{"kind":"text","text":"] the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":"of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eatamap","text_ar":"عَتَمَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EatamapF","text_ar":"عَتَمَةً"},{"kind":"text","text":"] being elided. (TA. [But"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EatamN","text_ar":"عَتَمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is also mentioned in the TA, in the beginning of this art., not as being originally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EatamapN","text_ar":"عَتَمَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", but simply as a subst. in the sense expl. above.])       -A2-  [Also, in its most usual sense,] The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"first third of the night, after the disappearance of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$afaq","text_ar":"شَفَق"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"redness that is seen in the sky after sunset"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (Kh, S, Msb, K;) the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"first part"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the night,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"after the setting of the light of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$afaq","text_ar":"شَفَق"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Msb:) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"time of the prayer of nightfall:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K:) but the calling of that prayer the prayer of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eatamap","text_ar":"عَتَمَة"},{"kind":"text","text":", as the Arabs of the desert called it, instead of calling it the prayer of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ei$aA='","text_ar":"عِشَا=ء"},{"kind":"text","text":", is said to be forbidden in a trad. (TA.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eatamapu rubaEK","text_ar":"عَتَمَةُ رُبَعٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Etmp","text_ar":"عتمة"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of a young camel brought forth in the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rabiyE","text_ar":"رَبِيع"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"which is the beginning of the breeding-time"},{"kind":"text","text":"], (S, K,) meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the space during which it"},{"kind":"text","text":"(i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rubaE","text_ar":"رُبَع"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"is confined at its evening-feed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K,) is applied to"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the moonlight of the night when the moon is four nights old."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K.) AZ says, The Arabs say in relation to the moon when it is one night old,"},{"kind":"page_break","n":1950},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eatamapu suxayolapK Hal~a A^aholuhaA birumayolapK","text_ar":"عَتَمَةُ سُخَيْلَةٍ حَلَّ اَهْلُهَا بِرُمَيْلَةٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Etmp","text_ar":"عتمة"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of a little lamb"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"kid, the owners of which have alighted in a small tract of sand"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; meaning that it does not long continue; like the lamb, or kid, that sucks its mother and soon returns to the sucking: and when it is two nights old,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hadiyvu A^amatayoni","text_ar":"حَدِيثُ اَمَتَيْنِ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bika*ibK wamayonK","text_ar":"بِكَذِبٍ وَمَيْنٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The discourse of two female slaves, with lying and falsehood"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; because their discourse is not long, by reason of their being busied with the serving of their owners: and when it is three nights old,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hadiyvu fatayaAtK gayori muw^otalifaAtK","text_ar":"حَدِيثُ فَتَيَاتٍ غَيْرِ مُوْتَلِفَاتٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The discourse of young women not united by affection"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: and when it is four nights old,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eatamapu rubaEK gayori jaAy^iEK","text_ar":"عَتَمَةُ رُبَعٍ غَيْرِ جَايِعٍ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"walaA muroDaEK","text_ar":"وَلَا مُرْضَعٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Etmp","text_ar":"عتمة"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rbE","text_ar":"ربع"},{"kind":"text","text":"(expl. above)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"not hungry nor suckled"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; meaning that it is limited to the space of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fuwaAq","text_ar":"فُوَاق"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or time between two suckings] of this"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rbE","text_ar":"ربع"},{"kind":"text","text":"or of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fwAq","text_ar":"فواق"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or time between two milkings] of its mother; or, as IAar says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eatamapu A^um~i Alr~ubaEi","text_ar":"عَتَمَةُ اُمِّ الرُّبَعِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Etmp","text_ar":"عتمة"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the mother of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rbE","text_ar":"ربع"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: and when it is five nights old,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HadiyvN waA^unosN wabaqaA='u Ea$aA='i xalifaAtK quEosK","text_ar":"حَدِيثٌ وَاُنْسٌ وَبَقَا=ءُ عَشَا=ءِ خَلِفَاتٍ قُعْسٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Discourse and sociableness, and the continuance of the evening-feed of pregnant camels having their heads and necks inclining towards their backs:"},{"kind":"text","text":"see also art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qEs","text_ar":"قعس"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: and when it is six nights old,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yasorN wabat~N","text_ar":"يَسْرٌ وَبَتٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[app. A twisting and a grinding by"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a turning towards the left and from the left;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as though meaning that it is a time fit for active employment]: and when it is seven nights old,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dulojapu","text_ar":"دُلْجَةُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlD~abuEi","text_ar":"الضَّبُعِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The night-journeying of the hyena"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: and when it is eight nights old,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qamarN A_iDoHiyaAnN","text_ar":"قَمَرٌ اـِضْحِيَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A bright moon"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: and when it is nine nights old,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yuloqaTu fiyhi","text_ar":"يُلْقَطُ فِيهِ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AljazoEu","text_ar":"الجَزْعُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The onyx is picked up in it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"being distinguishable by the light of the moon]: and when it is ten nights old,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muxan~iqu Alfajori","text_ar":"مُخَنِّقُ الفَجْرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[lit."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The choker of the dawn;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as though its light were about to overtake, and grapple with, that of daybreak]. (TA.) [It should be observed that every one of these ten sayings is fancifully framed so as to rhyme, perfectly or imperfectly, with words preceding it: the first being preceded by"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aibonu layolapK","text_ar":"اِبْنُ لَيْلَةٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; the second, by"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aibonu layolatayoni","text_ar":"اِبْنُ لَيْلَتَيْنِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; the third, by"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aibonu","text_ar":"اِبْنُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"valaAvK","text_ar":"ثَلَاثٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; the fourth, by"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aibonu A^arobaEK","text_ar":"اِبْنُ اَرْبَعٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and so on.] ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EatamapN","text_ar":"عَتَمَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies also The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"darkness"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the night: (S, K, TA:) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"darkness of the first part of the night,"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"after nightfall,"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e.]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"after the setting of the light of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$afaq","text_ar":"شَفَق"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"redness that is seen in the sky after sunset"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: and the vulgar [sometimes] pronounce it"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eatomap","text_ar":"عَتْمَة"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) ―         -b4-  And The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"remains of the milk that has collected in the udders of the camels,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the camels and other cattle, at the period thus termed."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, ISd, K.) One says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HalabonaA EatamapF","text_ar":"حَلَبْنَا عَتَمَةً"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"We milked some remains of what had collected in the udders"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]. (S, TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hulibato EatamatuhaA","text_ar":"حُلِبَتْ عَتَمَتُهَا"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The milk that was obtained from them at the period termed the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eatamap","text_ar":"عَتَمَة"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"was drawn."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA, from the trad. of Aboo-Dharr.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaEada EinodanaA fulaAnN qadora Eatamapi AlHalaAy^ibi","text_ar":"قَعَدَ عِنْدَنَا فُلَانٌ قَدْرَ عَتَمَةِ الحَلَايِبِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e. ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one sat with us,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"at our abode,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"as long as the space during which the milch camels are confined for the purpose of the collecting of the milk in their udders."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b5-  And The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"return of the camels from the place of pasturing after their entering upon evening."},{"kind":"text","text":"(ISd, K.)"}],"source_refs":["IB","TA","Msb","S","K"]}]},"classical_definitions":{"source":"hawramani","url":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/%D8%B9%D8%AA%D9%85%D8%A9/","headword_ar":"عُتُمَةُ","entries":[{"lexicon_id":"dictionary_52","lexicon_en":"Yāqūt al-Ḥamawī, Muʿjam al-Buldān (d. 1229)","lexicon_ar":"معجم البلدان لياقوت الحموي","permalink":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/?p=144076#19acc7","body_html":"عُتُمَةُ:<br>مضموم: حصن في جبال وصاب من أعمال زبيد."}]}}